  <!-- Use paragraphs to break apart subsections -->
    <paragraphs>
      <title>What do we do in MATH-262?</title>

      <p>
        The course catalog describes this course simply lists this class as covering “Exact solutions of common types of first-order ordinary differential equations, linear equations of higher order, power series solutions, Laplace transforms, linear systems including matrix methods, graphical and numerical techniques and applications of differential equations.”
      </p>
      <p>
        I believe this description misses the bigger picture from Differential Equations. These types of equations model countless real-world phenomena, as they can describe characteristics of real systems that change throughout time and space. This course is the study of modelling such phenomena. 
      </p>
      
    </paragraphs>
